THE PROJECT MUST FOCUS ACTIVITIES IN THE USAID/INDONESIA PRIORITY PROVINCES FOR HIV/AIDS, AS IDENTIFIED USING KEY CRITERIA FROM A 2013 SITUATION ANALYSIS OF THE HIV EPIDEMIC IN INDONESIA, OF JAKARTA, EAST JAVA, WEST JAVA, CENTRAL JAVA, NORTH SUMATERA, RIAU ISLAND, PAPUA, AND WEST PAPUA.

column28: IGF::CT::IGF. THIS IS AN ACQUISITION PLAN FOR HYBRID (FIXED PRICE, TIME AND MATERIAL, AND LABOR HOUR) COMMERCIAL SERVICES. THE PRIMARY PROJECTED OUTCOME WILL DEVELOP, SUPPORT, AND IMPLEMENT FEDERAL DISASTER RECOVERY INITIATIVES.  EXAMPLES OF THE INITIATIVES ARE AS FOLLOWS:  SUPPORTING POLICY AND DOCTRINE DEVELOPMENT; RESEARCH; PROVIDING TECHNICAL SUPPORT, PLANNING FOR FIELD OPERATIONS; DEVELOPING AND CONDUCTING PROGRAM EVALUATIONS; DEVELOPING AND MAINTAINING TRAINING MATERIALS AND STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES; AND PLANNING FOR CONFERENCES.  THE GOVERNMENT PLANS TO AWARD A BPA WITH A ONE YEAR BASE AND FOUR (4) OPTION YEARS.  PERIOD OF PERFORMANCE IS ANTICIPATED 12/03/2015 THROUGH 12/03/2016.
